</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Not a long term player, been here about a year or so but have played my shaman into the elementals so i have at least seen some of the issues first hand. My point is that I came in after many of these nerfs took place, so I do not know life before the Beastlord, or mitigating slow, as examples.<br />
<br />
While I don't think it devalues my opinion I think it makes it harder for me to understand your frustrations. I enjoy playing my Shaman but am not naive enough to miss the fact that you old timers are angry and there must be a reason. <br />
<br />
How about the site admins do something radical here. Open a post that folks can nominate people for Shaman council. Then, after a week run a voting booth. One week passes and you can have your council. Those folks can prepare an outline of how the Shaman community feels as a whole and present it for edit.<br />
<br />
Then go ahead and pursue changes. We should be able to find a common ground, but open forum is not going to work. At least not from watching the boards for a long time.<br />
<br />
At least use this as a base for trying to set up a common voice before you cry "F-off noob".<br />
<br />
Thanks,</p>
	
	
	
	
	
