	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Hurrk</b><br /><i>I made this post because I am weary of the continual class devaluation that comes with every expansion.  Because we have slipped not only from our one time position of very good class power, but to quite possibly below the very bottom tier.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I find that statement to be a bit ridiculous.  Shaman are far from the bottom of the barrel.<br />
<br />
Raiding can be a big part of the game but not everybody raids and I don't think you can base the value of a class on one type of situation.  It seems like the only real serious complaint anyone ever makes about shaman is in regards to raiding - and even then it's usually something like, 'I cannot do this, but I can do this or this or this,' which indicates that as always, a resourceful shaman can find a way to contribute.<br />
<br />
What class really does anything amazing on a raid?  You have one MT, so all the rest of the tanks are just autoattacking...woopee.  Clerics are just gonna be healing...and probably in some kind of rotation - boy, that's thrilling.  Pet classes and nukers send their pets - and hope the critter isn't totally magic resistant reducing them to bystanders.  I have no clue what druids do...  It would seem that most classes have limited roles in raids only a few people in any given raid are really gonna have a truly significant role.  It would seem that if your raid force is so big that you have several shaman than it's more of a zerg than anything...<br />
<br />
And, yes, I would say that any class that can solo (with ease based on the tales posted here) in the elemental planes isn't very likely to be getting any kind of significant boost in power.  How many classes can solo the elemental planes with ease?  How do you boost a class in a significant way without making it more powerful as a soloist?<br />
<br />
In a normal xp group situation we have numerous possible roles.<br />
<br />
I think some folks that've seen everything and done everything 10x over are maybe just a bit bored, which leads to much more complaining and stating of unrealistic expectations on forums!</p>
	
	
	
