	<!-- message -->
	<p>Things are hardly doom and gloom, but anyone who is prepared to scream that we have not been mitigated as a class since Kunark hasn't been playing since Kunark and can't appreciate why it's being said.<br />
<br />
Yes, the new slow line is exactly what many of us wanted and finally lends a gentle push of credibility to our "king of the slow spells" title.  It will have an interesting effect on raiding and grouping in DPS groups, but much of the focus is on DoTs.  I don't think the planned expansion really screws us as the crit DoTs, and the new DoT series (which I expect they will improve, hence the OK comment to follow) are OK, but show a total lack of understanding of what MOST of the shaman community really does.  Most of us nuke and heal when we're not out debuffing the MoBs of Norrath and our nukes have fallen even further behind everyone else's with this expansion.  MOST of us have little or no nead for another long term DoT.  I have very few beefs about these planned abilities and spells other than I'll never use them.  If I don't use them, I haven't gained anything and my class is further mitigated.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
