	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Face it, with the new expansion, and the tempted fate of putting the regen of what replaced stamina on shaman, they are delegating us to buff bots.  Now we have three functions on a riad<br />
<br />
1) MGB focus<br />
2) slow the mob<br />
3) regen the melees stamina<br />
<br />
This will do one of two things.<br />
<br />
1) with the limited amount of "good playing" shaman out there you will become a commodity to be wanted.<br />
<br />
or (the reality)<br />
<br />
2) people will make shaman bots and PL the hell out of them just so their raid can have the necessary buffs.<br />
<br />
Looking at the aa's every class gets something that makes them more unique, except us, we get jack and unless we as a community do something, like the warriors did, we are going to continue to be sold down the river.<br />
<br />
either way you feel, we need to be fixed, we used to be the jack of all trades, but with the upcoming aa's we are going to be a questionable use and the stigma of "are you a bot or a real shaman" will come up more often as with clerics.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
