<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Boinshar</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Prophet of War<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2000<br />
	Location: Springfield Va USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>There are two main reasons preventing the shaman class from uniting.<br />
<br />
1. We don't know what we want<br />
<br />
Individually we know exactly what we want. Each and every one of us has an idea of how to improve the shaman class. However, the vast gear, experience, and play style differences among us make it impossible for us to form a consensus.<br />
<br />
The more experienced players cannot convince the less experienced players that they are right, because the only reason they can come up with is "I know better than you, just listen to what I say". Obviously, that reason doesn't work so well, even though it has a grain of truth. Conversely, casual players accuse hard core players that their gear blinds them to what the shaman class truly needs. Again, obviously this reason isn't received well, but it also holds a grain of truth.<br />
<br />
What is the result? As collective, we are completely clueless.<br />
<br />
2. People don't know what they are talking about.<br />
<br />
There, I said it. I do not say this as an accusation, but as a fact. How many times have you read a post that in essence agrees with your point, and said to yourself "I wish this person would shut up, because he's hurting my cause" because the content of the post did not support the conclusion?<br />
<br />
There are many people out there with the passion for change, but are unable or unwilling to support their claims with facts. As a result, posts containing wild exaggerations and ridiculous claims abound on the Crucible these days. How can one hope garner support from the community with logic and reasons while surrounded by a horde of raving lunatics?<br />
<br />
3. What do we do to fix it?<br />
<br />
I have no idea.<br />
<br />
EDIT: Ok, that's not entirely true. I just don't see any reason to use the time and effort to come up with a solution at this point.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Boinshar Harlishambar</div>
	
