	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>nuzum</b><br /><i><br />
<br />
1) MGB focus<br />
2) slow the mob<br />
3) regen the melees stamina<br />
<br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I think part of the problem stems from the idea that we're somehow entitled to do more than those 3 things.  The way I see it, Everquest is ultimately a very simple game.  Nobody really has much of anything to do at a raid.  What does a rogue do?  Stand behind something, hit autoattack and press their backstab hotkey for 5 minutes.  What does a wizard do?  Hit their highest nuke every 30 seconds so they don't get turned into a splat on the wall.  What does a druid do?  Nothing! Haha, but seriously, they heal and do some damage.  Everybody is a one trick pony at a raid, its the combination of tricks between different classes that makes things at all interesting.  <br />
<br />
<br />
We MGB focus, slow and debuff the target, and then spot heal and toss on what dps we can.  That seems like a fair shake to me.  My complaint is the same as many other folks here: most of our abilities are arguably no longer of the same quality as other classes.  If you're bored of your EQ niche, thats probably more because EQ is really kind of a boring game in a lot of ways than a problem with the niche itself.</p>
	
	
	
