	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>darkpaw</b><br /><i>I definately haven't seen and done everything, but even I realize as a class we are falling significantly behind.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I am in the same boat.  I have only been playing EQ for a little over a year and just got my Shaman to lvl 65.  I have been more and more frustrated as I leveled past 50.  <br />
<br />
Where I was once the 2cd best healer in the game, after the mid 50's I become a very lame third.  I would like to see us be at least on par with druid heals.<br />
<br />
Currently, I spend more time canabalizing myself than I do actually casting spells.  Don't know what the answer to this one is.<br />
<br />
My combat abilities are a joke.  I have maxed out my pierce, 1hb and offense and still if I can get one hit to land in HoH I consider myself lucky.  I don't know what SOE has done to cause this but I would like to be able to hit the mobs occasionally.<br />
<br />
It seems to me that the only ability that we have as a class is that of Slow, but we also share that with necros and chanters.  I understand that each class shares certain abilities with other classes but why is it that Shaman have nothing that is uniquely ours.  I am really tired of feeling that the only reason I am there is to cast focus and slow.  Heck, I almost was kicked out of a group yesterday because I didn't have FA yet!  <br />
<br />
Personally, I often don't see the reason for having a shaman in a good group.  The mobs die to quick for us to use our dots.  We are the worst healers in the game.  Chanters and BSTs can slow almost as good as we can.  Our DD is slow, mana inefiecient and low damage.  What is left for us to do?  The only decent thing that I have seen for me since I started was Bane, but that takes 650 adv pts in a theme that noone wants to go in.  <br />
<br />
I would love to see some of this changed...I just don't know how to do it.  Point me in the direction and I am there.  I love my shaman and have spent lots of time playing him up to 65.  I was never PL'd and never twinked, so I have a special love of the class and can't stand to see them passed up yet again.</p>
	
	
	
