	<p>Druids united, made a big long thread with lots of bold text and numbers and stuff, and they got damn near every ****ing item on the list.<br />
<br />
Warriors got every other class to complain about them, and got something pretty decent (now fix the damn MM dagger proc to not overwrite it  <img src="images/smilies/mad.gif" border="0" alt="" title="mad" smilieid="9" /> <br />
<br />
We need to decide on something, and fast. Right now, <b>The only valid concerns are the following two:</b><br />
<br />
1) Reduce Marginalization of our enhanced mana generation,<br />
<br />
and<br />
<br />
2) Give us a method of dealing damage that supports the above.<br />
<br />
Solutions:<br />
<br />
1) Either reduce the mana cost for stuff we cast, add resist modifiers (or an innate malisement AA), or increase the Effect. Very simple.<br />
<br />
2) a DoT spell that drains mana as it deals damage would be cool, in that it ends when the mob dies. There could be an initial mana cost to get it going, and you could choose when to stop it from going.<br />
<br />
or<br />
<br />
Increase the length of fights significantly, and jack up the experience accordingly.<br />
<br />
Double attack and bash wouldn't hurt either ^_^</p>
	
	
	
