	<p>To be honest I don't think shaman ever really had a class identity. They were effectively the "total melee support package" for those races that didn't have priests and chanters. Torpor / Canni is effectively our version of KEI (why would we need a group one? the rest of the race classes are going to be melee). The class power is almost entirely connected to the fact that slow proved to be brokenly powerful and to become ever more powerful as mobs scale.<br />
<br />
I honestly believe the shaman class needs a substantial re-design. The class goal and spells are a bit of a mess and lack identity. In addition with more mana regen and SoE trying to reduce the power of slow (which they need to) our old advantages continue to ablate.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
