<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Chifari</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Hurrk</b><br /><i><br />
I'm not gonna analyze the AA list offered for us in GoD.  I won't do it for new spells either.  However, I think its kinda clear the shaman devaluation continues.<br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Agreed, although it isn't clear other classes really get much out of GoD either.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Hurrk</b><br /><i><br />
Perhaps what I dislike the most about our devaluation though is that so many people that post in this site resist organizing Shaman players to ask for significant change.  I have speculated there are SOE employees posting here in the guise of players, it has been so strongly worded.<br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I think a lot of this comes from the fact that when I turn around and look at clerics and druids, no matter how much they give them, I *still* feel like the most powerful class.  I know clerics and druids heal and nuke a lot better (and the gap is widening), but I still feel like DoTs, slow, and insane mana regen make shaman the best of the three classes.  Am I living in the past or denial?  Maybe.  I haven't done parses to see how my damage stacks up to the other two.  But I've played both druid and cleric, and soloing alone imo gives us the edge over clerics in terms of 'fun'... druid is tougher; they may be as good/better than shammies now.  I don't know.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Hurrk</b><br /><i><br />
The list of class nerfs/ability sharing to other classes is legion.  Dating all the way back to our charm nerf, if anyone here actually remembers that.  Ok, so they have nerfed us out and shared away all our unique class abilites.  How about something new?  Well, really, I dont think we have seen anything significantly new since Focus, and that was what, 5 expansions ago counting GoD?<br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Well, this is something of an exaggeration.  Luclin gave us Canni5, PoP gave us pet swarm, dots that don't break root, knockback root, and radiant cure.  And, love it or hate it, LoY gave us a unique thing in Blood of Nadox.<br />
<br />
But I see your point and somewhat agree with it.  I think that shamans were quite overpowered compared to clr/dru around the time of Luclin.  With PoP, I think they were so concerned about the shaman mana regen power that they really swung the nerf bat hard, going overboard merely by *not* giving us a good cold nuke (among other things).  That fear (that shamans are overpowered) seems to continue to this day... they're afraid to give us anything good because of our mana regen.  All they'd have to do is make it cost a ton to balance it, too (e.g. 1200 nuke for 500 mana).  <br />
<br />
We also had to deal with the introduction of the BST, which devalued us somewhat.  But I still think a well-geared shm owns a well-geared bst.  Their dps is actually pretty close (when doing nothing but), and the shaman can solo things the beast can't dream of doing.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Hurrk</b><br /><i><br />
Once upon a time, our debuffs made us critical to raiding guilds.  Now...lots of people can debuff, we just need to make sure we can MGB Focus.  Yes, that does describe a BOT more than a primary player class.  And yes, that does tend to lend more momentum to the concept of switching to BST.<br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I would add nadox to that list of critical things shaman do, but yeah, that isn't much (only a few fights here and there), and it's not like other classes can't cure, too (although a bit less effectively).<br />
  <blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Hurrk</b><br /><i><br />
I made this post because I am weary of the continual class devaluation that comes with every expansion.  Because we have slipped not only from our one time position of very good class power, but to quite possibly below the very bottom tier.  <br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I disagree with this, though... maybe you're just depressed about GoD (and I don't blame you).  But shaman were near the top of the game around Velious.  Now they've slipped to somewhere in the middle.  But no way are they near the bottom.  They're still a supremely flexible class (solo well, get groups easy).  I think it's mainly our raid importance that has been diminished so far, and, as a raiding shaman, you feel that very acutely.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Hurrk</b><br /><i><br />
But mostly because I am seeing once again how so many of you are unhappy with yet another offering of crap in a new expansion.....and so many more of you are all set to once again try to defuse the unhappiness and convince people it's all ok, that we're just fine, that we are superbly balanced.<br />
<br />
Do you still really believe this?  Once upon a time the shaman class united, and made some changes.  Remember the epic?  Honestly, take a good look at what you have got since Velious.  Look at how other classes have changed since Velious.  Think about it.  If you like it, ok.  I just disagree with you, but I won't try to convince you.  But if not, can you give some thought to trying to get something significantly new and useful for us?  Restore to the class some greater value than being a MGB Focus BOT?  Yes, perhaps a united voice is a lost cause.....but somehow I like trying better than laying down.<br />
<br />
Or we can just do nothing at all.  And it will just be how it is.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I think the first step would be, as others have noted, to agree on what we'd actually want.  A lot of the problem is that shammies can do so many things... it's hard to pick which one of them to pick to improve upon.  <br />
<br />
Even improving our pets (the approach Sony has taken with GoD) doesn't have to be a bad idea, but if they were going to go that route, why not go all out?  Give us a better pet, a new pet spell, make them dual wield innately, give a dps upgrade, etc.  Otherwise, those upgrades are pointless.<br />
<br />
Personally, I think shaman nukes being so close to rangers' is just stupid; 925 is way too low, especially if clerics/chanters get new nukes in GoD.  925 was a kneejerk/overkill number, and doing things like putting Spear of Torment focus on elemental gloves didn't help.  Our nuking is a little (not a lot, but a little) below where it should be.  <br />
<br />
Any sort of upgrade to canni/slow/cripple would have been nice, although let's face it: upgrading cripple wouldn't be some huge change (though so many seem to clamor for it).<br />
<br />
Anyway, I *do* think the GoD aas look pretty miserable, but I take some comfort in the fact they look miserable for lots of other classes, too.  I still think shaman is a great class.<br />
<br />
chif</p>
	
	
	
	
	
